xcel files work with both the older xls format (Excel 2003 and earlier) and the newer xlsx format (Excel 2007 and later).\n\nReviewing my findings: V3 has two phantom sections with minimal content (s3 and s5 with \"なし\"), V4 is missing the \"Matcher\" class name in s1 hints, and s3 hints in V4 are too generic. s1 is missing \"Matcher\" from the hints since it's a PascalCase class name directly referenced in the content. I'll skip reporting the s3 and s5 hints issues separately since the underlying section content problems already cover those. Let me do one final check for any critical gaps or inaccuracies—the image in the framework composition section can't be represented textually so that's fine, and the table captures the structural details. I'm noticing that s1 mentions specific annotations like @Test and @Before under JUnit4 features, but the source only says \"various annotations\" in that section—those specific names come from a later section on test method writing, which is cross-section synthesis within the same document.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20649,"cache_read_input_tokens":29807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20649,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d97e26ba-5f45-47bd-8521-4430b43412b5","uuid":"ade6103c-2bb9-4768-8bfb-3e5fd245a78d"}
